What is a Continuous Glucose Monitoring (CGM) System?
A Continuous Glucose Monitoring (CGM) system is an advanced medical device that continuously measures glucose levels throughout the day and night, enabling patients and healthcare professionals to monitor blood sugar trends in real time. Unlike conventional fingerstick testing, CGM devices use a small wearable sensor placed beneath the skin that wirelessly transmits glucose data to a receiver, smartphone, or insulin pump.
Modern CGM systems provide predictive alerts for high and low glucose levels, helping users make timely decisions regarding insulin therapy, nutrition, and physical activity. These technologies are becoming an essential component of personalized diabetes management by improving glycemic control while reducing complications associated with fluctuating blood glucose levels.
